#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/server-dedup-props.md
M|rules|title: Avoid Duplicate Serialization in RSC Props
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: reduces network payload by avoiding duplicate serialization
M|rules|tags: server, rsc, serialization, props, client-components
M|rules|**Impact: LOW (reduces network payload by avoiding duplicate serialization)**
M|rules|RSC→client serialization deduplicates by object reference, not value. Same reference = serialized once; new reference = serialized again. Do transformations (`.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`) in c
M|rules|**Incorrect (duplicates array):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// RSC: sends 6 strings (2 arrays × 3 items)
M|rules|<ClientList usernames={usernames} usernamesOrdered={usernames.toSorted()} />
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (sends 3 strings):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// RSC: send once
M|rules|<ClientList usernames={usernames} />
M|rules|// Client: transform there
M|rules|'use client'
M|rules|const sorted = useMemo(() => [...usernames].sort(), [usernames])
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Nested deduplication behavior:**
M|rules|Deduplication works recursively. Impact varies by data type:
M|rules|- `string[]`, `number[]`, `boolean[]`: **HIGH impact** - array + all primitives fully duplicated
M|rules|- `object[]`: **LOW impact** - array duplicated, but nested objects deduplicated by reference
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// string[] - duplicates everything
M|rules|usernames={['a','b']} sorted={usernames.toSorted()} // sends 4 strings
M|rules|// object[] - duplicates array structure only
M|rules|users={[{id:1},{id:2}]} sorted={users.toSorted()} // sends 2 arrays + 2 unique objects (not 4)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Operations breaking deduplication (create new references):**
M|rules|- Arrays: `.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`, `.slice()`, `[...arr]`
M|rules|- Objects: `{...obj}`, `Object.assign()`, `structuredClone()`, `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())`
M|rules|**More examples:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// ❌ Bad
M|rules|<C users={users} active={users.filter(u => u.active)} />
M|rules|<C product={product} productName={product.name} />
M|rules|// ✅ Good
M|rules|<C users={users} />
M|rules|<C product={product} />
M|rules|// Do filtering/destructuring in client
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Exception:** Pass derived data when transformation is expensive or client doesn't need original.